    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "There is such a thing as giving unwise help to our children. Those who work their way through college appreciate their advantages more than those who are provided with them at someone else&apos;s expense, for they know their cost. We must not carry our children until they become helpless burdens.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 50, 1895\" data-link=\"14060.6922001\">Letter 50, 1895</span>.</span></a></sup>",
