    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Parents mistake their duty when they freely hand out money to any youth who has physical strength to enter on a course of study to become a minister or a physician before he has had an experience in useful, taxing labor.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">7<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 103, 1900\" data-link=\"14065.9863001\">Letter 103, 1900</span>.</span></a></sup>",
